Carl Sagan:  There are some hundred billion galaxies , each with , on the average , a hundred billion stars , 1011 x 1011 = 1022 , _ ten _ billion trillion . We are just beginning our explorations . From eight billion light - years away we are hard pressed to find even the cluster in which our Milky Way Galaxy is embedded , much less the Sun or the Earth .
